annotationA: 40S ribosomal protein S2; Has a specific developmental role during oogenesis and a general role in protein synthesis as a component of the small ribosomal subunit
annotationB: Ribosomal protein L38 is a component of the large subunit of cytoplasmic ribosomes, which translate mRNAs encoded by the nuclear genome. The gene is haploinsufficient - heterozygous mutants display the 'Minute' phenotype, characterized by a slower developmental rate and small adult bristles
